title: Parent Teacher Student Association at Frisco Elementary launches online silent auction
text:
Parent Teacher Student Association at Frisco Elementary launches online silent auction
The Parent Teacher Student Association at Frisco Elementary has launched an online silent auction in order to help fund initiatives at the school.
All of the proceeds from the auction will go to fund field trips, school-wide events, classroom enhancements and support the school’s teachers. The online auction launched on Tuesday, Dec. 3 and will run through Wednesday, Dec. 11 at 9 p.m.
The silent auction includes items from a number of local businesses like Gentlemen’s Barbershop, Ruby Jane, Daylight Donuts, Breck Create, Deli Belly’s, Next Page Books, Foote’s Rest, Arapahoe Basin Ski Area, Loveland Ski Area, Copper Mountain Resort and more.
Items can be picked up at Frisco Elementary on Thursday, Dec. 12, Friday, Dec. 13 or Monday, Dec. 16 from 3-5 p.m.
To bid on an item, visit CharityAuctionsToday.com/bid/FRE2024
